KW  - Supply equation
KW  - Real exchange rate
KW  - Cointegration
KW  - Homogeneity tests
KW  - Purchasing power parity
AB  - Using price and wage equations, an aggregate supply relationship is derived, which relates domestic to foreign prices and output. It is shown that, among all parameters, only the degree of wage indexation matters to the question of whether the nominal exchange rate can affect competitiveness. Cointegration results support the existence of a long-run relationship among the variables of the model which is in conformity with the relationship derived in the theoretical part of the paper. Empirical analysis (a) does not confirm relative Purchase Power Parity for Greek wholesale price indices, and (b) does not contradict the hypothesis that Greek producer prices are homogeneous of degree one in foreign prices.
